Mini Footprints 

SaaS-Based E-Commerce Store

Built by: Mamata Pokharel | BSc.CSIT, St. Xavier's College, Kathmandu | Course: E-Commerce 6th Semester | Platform: Blanxer (SaaS e-commerce CMS) | Status: Built and fully operational during the platform's free trial period; 
the store is no longer hosted. Screenshots of the storefront, admin panel, and analytics dashboards are included in /screenshots.

Overview
Mini Footprints is a fully functional e-commerce store for baby party shoes, built end-to-end on the Blanxer SaaS platform. The project covers the complete lifecycle of launching a niche online retail business in Nepal 
from market research and business modelling to storefront build, payment integration, analytics setup, and search visibility.The target segment is parents of children aged 0–5 shopping for footwear for birthdays, weddings,
and festive occasions. A Business Model Canvas was developed first (customer segments, value proposition, channels, revenue streams, cost structure) and used to drive the store's structure and messaging.

What I built
a.	Storefront: custom-branded homepage, category architecture (Baby Boy / Baby Girl / Unisex), product listing and detail pages, filters, cart, and checkout
b.	Product catalogue: listings with descriptions, sizing guides, media, and discount pricing
c.	Payments: eSewa, Khalti, and Cash on Delivery integration with automated order confirmation
d.	SEO: page-level meta titles, meta descriptions, image optimisation, and a searchable category structure to improve organic discoverability
e.	Analytics: Google Analytics 4 and Google Tag Manager configured to track traffic sources, user acquisition, retention, engagement, and new vs. returning users
f.	Customer engagement: Tawk.to live chat plugin and automated SMS notifications for each order status

Key takeaways
Practical, hands-on exposure to how site structure, metadata, and analytics data connect directly to traffic and conversions plus the discipline of measuring what a store does rather than assuming it.


